&gt;&gt; The other approach is to add a profile link to each of the resources
&gt;&gt; which points to a URI which works much the same way as the link
&gt;&gt; relation type above i.e. inferring info/state/semantics.
&gt;&gt;
&gt;
&gt; but doesn&#39;t that require the client having to consume the entire doc first?

Yes it does, which may or may not be suitable for your use case. Of
course, this isn&#39;t something the first option suffers from.

&gt;
&gt; ~~~
&gt; As a third option, how about using a &quot;profile&quot; parameter, as per the idea in
&gt; [1], ie:
&gt;
&gt; Content-Type: application/hal+json;profile=&quot;com.mycompany.myapp.Order&quot;
&gt;

Sure that&#39;s also possible.

fwiw, I generally try to avoid putting app-specific things like this
in the headers because they &quot;take more effort to get at&quot;, and
intermediaries can do nasty things with the headers which will
introduce bugs in your app.

Cheers,
M
